
Create a relative date
```sh
date --date 'tomorrow 0830'
date --date 'today 0830'
```

Format a date ISO8601
```sh
date -Iseconds
date -Iminutes
```

Format a date ISO8601 Zulu
```sh
date '+%FT%TZ'
date '+%FT%T.000Z'
```

See also:
https://www.linuxjournal.com/content/doing-date-math-command-line-part-i
